<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1506.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-06T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1915—4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Replying yours March 3, 6 p.m., Department has informed Minister Jimenez
                            that it would sanction money for repairs Dominican Central Railroad
                            provided same be expended by director general public works and that
                            railroad, after repairs be operated by public works.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>